post_text: The Revere Class of 2020 will graduate on June 27th at 10:00am in front of the school's main entrance. "The gathering" consists of only Revere staff, immediate family members, and the graduates. Their seating will be provided on school grounds. Graduates should arrive by 9am. Immediate family members (not community members or extended family) of the graduates should arrive by 9:30am. As part of "the gathering" these people will need to have a health screen completed prior to the ceremony. Please park in the student parking lot and you will be given instructions by a Revere staff member. All others wishing to attend will not be considered as part of "the gathering" and will be asked to bring their own lawn chair and find a space on main street or in city park across the street. The road will be blocked off so please find parking south of the school on main street. All in attendance are asked to observe appropriate social distancing.

post_text: We would like to recognize the outstanding work related to implementation of a new program. STAR - Strategies for Teaching Based on Autism Research. Many school districts and staff members embraced a new leadership role this year implementing a curriculum for students with autism. Implementation of the Autism STAR curriculum required a staff member to take the lead role in this process as the team leader. Staff participated in several days of training to learn about the program, and began to use it with the students chosen to benefit from the program. Through this leadership, the team working with their team leaders also gained the opportunity to show their strengths and strong desire to support students with Autism. Wonderful job Tiffany, Theresa, Jenna, Madi, Missy & Natasha!!

Community members, please sign up for a time to complete the QPR training.

Julesburg School District, Revere School District, and Sedgwick County Hospital have collaborated to discuss our collective concerns about mental health in our community. We are holding several QPR (Question Persuade Refer) training meetings for our staff and anyone who wants to join in. This will be a one hour suicide prevention training.

QPR zoom date options:

May 12th at 3pm

May 14th at 3pm

May 20th at 3pm

Please use this link (https://forms.gle/MbiPNZjNn1L42Cbv6) to sign-up for a date that works best for you. In response, we will send you an email with the zoom link to the training date you chose.

Today’s Rockstar Raider was nominated by not one, but TWO Revere staff members! Both Ms. Missy and Mrs. Sittner nominated Tristen Gonzales.

Ms. Missy says, “I am nominating Tristen as he has worked extremely hard the last 2 weeks and finished his homework early. I meet with Tristen at 8:00 am and he has only missed one of our meetings since we started. In addition to doing his school work he is responsible for making sure his 3 siblings make their meetings and stays on them about their school work.”

Mrs. Sittner said, “He has been getting all his work done with a positive attitude, and he's a great helper to his younger siblings!”

Great work Tristen!!

The staff of the Revere School District would like to take some time to recognize students who have done an incredible job adjusting to online learning. In order to do this, we have developed the "Rockstar Raider" award. We recognize that each of our students is working hard and adapting to this situation in their own way, and we are proud of each and every one of our students; however, teachers have nominated a few students who are going above and beyond expectations and requirements and doing exceptional work.

Today’s Rockstar Raider is Whitney Walter!

Mrs. Dykman nominated Whitney because, “Whitney has been a rockstar student, and through this transition she hasn’t skipped a beat! She continues to go above and beyond expectations and is encouraging and positive throughout our live sessions and online interactions.”

Keep it up Whit!!

As a community service project, the Revere School fifth-graders are collecting donations for the Adopt A Dog Animal Shelter in Chappell. Items needed include wet/dry dog and cat food. Also cat and dog toys, including Nylabones and Kong dog toys. Kitten season is around the corner, so kitten chow and fake fur for baby kittens are also appreciated. Items may be dropped off at Revere School in Ovid at the front office, or there is also a box set up in the elementary wing. Donations will be accepted until Friday, February 21st.
The dogs and cats thank you!

🚌Tuesday is Museum Overnight Field Trip Day for 3-5 Grades!! Students should come to school dressed in their comfortable clothes (they’ll be sleeping in them), and bring their sleeping bag, pillow, toothbrush, toothpaste and deodorant all in one large duffel or trash bag. Students also need to dress in layers as the temperature in the museum fluctuates. We will leave at 1:00 p.m on Tuesday and will return on Wednesday afternoon! It’s going to be a great trip!!!

Reminder: permission slips MUST be returned in order for students to attend.
